## 1. Install the knife windows plugin

You need to install the <codeinline>knife windows</codeinline> plugin on your workstation so that you can configure remote Windows Server nodes. Run this command to install it.

```bash
$ chef gem install knife-windows
```

## 2. Bootstrap your node

<div class="indent" id="bootstrap-intro">
From your workstation, run this command to bootstrap your node. If you're working with your own server and not the one that we provide, replace <codeinline>ADDRESS</codeinline> with your server's external address, <codeinline>USER</codeinline> with your username, and <codeinline>PASSWORD</codeinline> with your password.
</div>
